If immigration raids showed how security forces could be used against disfavored communities, a suite of executive orders showed how the same logic could be applied to identity itself. Executive Order 14168, signed on the first day of the term but documented in detail this week, ordered the federal government to \'93restore biological truth.\'94 In practice, it erased transgender people from official recognition. LGBTQ health pages and suicide-risk data were removed from federal websites. Trans-related terminology disappeared from surveys and guidance. The \'93X\'94 gender marker on passports was eliminated, and some passports were revoked. The Supreme Court allowed these rules to take effect while litigation continued. Knowledge itself was being rewritten. When a group is stripped from the data, its needs become easier to ignore and its suffering harder to prove.\
